snippet.textDisplay: It’s about love. It’s about a complicated relationship, struggling to have Glover’s partner commit—ultimately having the partner ask Glover to learn to live in the moment. This inability of Glover to let go is compared with his reflections and lamentations of losing his father—with all of the existential concerns that come with that. The album is capped off with Glover finding solace in life by turning to his role as a father. I don’t think you took your time with this, Fantanny.
snippet.textOriginal: It’s about love. It’s about a complicated relationship, struggling to have Glover’s partner commit—ultimately having the partner ask Glover to learn to live in the moment. snippet.textDisplay: Yup I knew it Donald Glover was literally disrespecting music production thinking he could drop this album as it is. I would give it a 5/10 as I liked some songs just not where they sit in the tracklist experience but it is underwhelming especially since, This America dropped. I understand why he gave it a 4.

snippet.textDisplay:
Definitely a mixed bag for me. Some songs morph into weird directions or an orgasm of sounds that just are really fucking jarring on certain songs. Think if he trimmed off the fat from the end of song of the songs, it'd be on par with Awaken My Love but I find myself listening to parts of songs only to skip to other parts of the record.

As someone who likes when albums flow very well (which this does in a way, but I don't like the way things transition at times), was sad it isn't as front to back oriented.

But there are some great influences on here perhaps some uninspired, like Prince, D'Angelo, even some Yeezus era sounds, Frank vibes on some pitch shifting, Andre 3000 etc. But it's definitely a messy album in many parts weighing down the highs.

Maybe it'll grow on me but for now it's a 5 or a 6 for me.

Edit: would be cool if it led to a larger more traditional album rollout with a more thoroughly explored direction of the sounds on this record but we'll see wouldn't be surprised if we don't get any more music for quite some time, let alone something entirely different.
